<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 03 at 3:36PM EDT  by NWS Columbia</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Lexington, northeastern Aiken and northern Orangeburg Counties
through 415 PM EDT...
At 336 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northeast of Aiken State Park, or 19 miles southeast of
Batesburg-Leesville, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Swansea, Wagener, Pelion, Perry, Perry Airport, Thor and Lexington
County Airport At Pelion.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
